      <title>Lowbie Mana Regen Issues?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Necromancers&amp;message.id=9522#M9522</link>
      <description>While playing with my new necro character on one of the progression servers recently, I noticed some very odd things.&amp;nbsp; I've tried searching for similar issues here, but haven't found too much to enlighten me.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;She is currently level 11.&amp;nbsp; (Yes, I have older necros on a few of the regular servers, but haven't actively played them since tSS release.)&amp;nbsp; Several days ago, I noticed that Dark Pact was suddenly eating her hps like mad even while sitting, which was never the case in the past.&amp;nbsp; However, since she seemed to be regenning mana quite nicely when in OOC mode, doing without it wasn't really slowing down my hunting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Tonight -- which was the first time I'd xp hunted with her since the last patch, rather than merely farming silk for her armor -- the OOC mana regen seemed horribly slow, however ... so I compared the regen rate between in-combat, during count-down, and out-of-combat.&amp;nbsp; The result was the same in each case.&amp;nbsp; In other words, she appeared to be getting no benefit from being in the OOC state.&amp;nbsp; So I tried Dark Pact again.&amp;nbsp; Lo and behold, it was more or less back to normal.&amp;nbsp; (I say "more or less," because the jerky movement in her hp bar gave me the impression that it's still eating hps like mad, but is now balanced out by OOC hp regen.&amp;nbsp; I didn't have it on during combat tonight, so I can't say for sure; will have to test it more thoroughly another time.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;She is pretty much untwinked except for an FBR (which is the only mana-related thing I've changed during the relevant period of time, but I can't see how that would make the difference).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Any thoughts?&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
