      <title>A request and suggestions for changes to lifeshards</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Necromancers&amp;message.id=9513#M9513</link>
      <description>I'm pretty sure it's clear that lifeshards need to be changed, at least for the majority of the necromancer community, so I have compiled a list of possible changes that might make everyone happy:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;A.)&amp;nbsp; Remove them from the game completely, and make our mezz use no reagent.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;B.)&amp;nbsp; Remove them from the game completely, and make our mezz use soul orbs as a reagent.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;C.)&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
Make lifeshards stackable, not lore, and not poof apon death.&amp;nbsp; Give&#xD;
them a different recast timer for their heal, and an instant cast for&#xD;
it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;D.)&amp;nbsp; Keep them lore, but take away the temporary tag, make&#xD;
them not poof on death, leave them as a reagent that doesn't get used&#xD;
up, and give them a much better heal (like the original way they were&#xD;
in the beta with a HoT potion effect).&amp;nbsp; This way they only go away if&#xD;
we use the lifeshard for healing purposes, and otherwise they stay&#xD;
around.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I would be equally pleased by any of the above&#xD;
solutions.&amp;nbsp; Some might be better than others because you can keep the&#xD;
animal only lifetaps in the game and thus keep you devs happy, and please the player base.&amp;nbsp; However, please give it some&#xD;
thought, we really need a change to this.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Aegrusnecrox&lt;br&gt;75 Necromancer of Maelin Starpyre&lt;br&gt;&amp;lt;PACTUM&amp;gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;P.S.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
