    <item>
      <title>Odd bug with Cloak of Shadows vs Ranger Shared Camouflage</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Necromancers&amp;message.id=9226#M9226</link>
      <description>I noticed this last night while I was in Sunderrock Springs. I had zoned into Sunderrock Spring and clicked my Cloak of Shadows AA and was running to catch up with my group who were already in zone near the mine enterance.  I caught up with them and we all decided to move to a different location to fight in the zone.  I was still invisible but the rest of the group was not as they had previously been fighting before I arrived. The ranger clicked her Shared Camouflage AA to invis the rest of the group.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We started to move to one of the cave areas when everything jumped me.  Now of course I feigned and the pet feigned, but everyone was puzzled as to why I was attacked?  Was it a see invis mob -- but why didn't it attack everyone else who ran by it first.  I waited for agro to clear, clicked CoS and stood up.  No agro.  I moved back to the group puzzled by what had happened.  So I called for an experiment being the inquisitive necromancer that I am.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Everyone became visible.  I clicked my Cloak of Shadows AA; I was invisible.  Then the ranger clicked her Shared Camouflage AA.  Now the group was invisible.  I got the message "Ledora tries to cast an invisibility spell on you, but you are already invisible."  Suddenly, I was visible.  YIKES!!  So that's what caused it the attack earlier.  I didn't get time to check this with other invisibilities, but I thought I would share my results so far. (and yes, I /bug-ged it.)</description>
