shaman, but I'll take my passive ability anyday), therefore when we run&#xD;
OOM while grouping there's probably something wrong/out of whack.&amp;nbsp; If&#xD;
they're going to give us 1300 mana cost dots, they should give us regen&#xD;
enough to be able to sustain casting them for a greater period of&#xD;
time.&amp;nbsp; Right now, with the discontinuance of affliction efficiency for&#xD;
72+ spells, our DPM took an enormous hit.&amp;nbsp; There's no way(to my&#xD;
knowledge) to account for that 23%(typically) of affliction&#xD;
efficiency/mana savings per cast for dots 72+, which coincidently have&#xD;
some of the largest mana cost(sans dreadpyre which is our 2nd most&#xD;
costly spell).&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The DPM on our spells was not updated&#xD;
sufficiently for the removal of that preservation.&amp;nbsp; Also, our mana&#xD;
regen wasn't upgraded to compensate for our spell cost(even if AE was&#xD;
updated and continued to 75).&amp;nbsp; There's a big list of reasons why we're&#xD;
running out of mana..and it's not just me, other necros in high end&#xD;
guilds I've spoken with have said the same thing.&lt;br&gt;---------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;PLASE address these issues.&amp;nbsp; Necros all over the game are finding it impossible to keep up with the cost of casting our new spells, and it is pointless having a class resorting to casting lower level spells than the best available because of a design fault that makes us simply unable to cast them in the way we were meant to.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is not a call to nerf anyone, but other classes got significant upgrades in the way they regen mana.&amp;nbsp; Necros did NOT, and it is desperately needed.&amp;nbsp; Please re-examine this matter carefully and upgrade lich (or reduce mana costs), and return the mana preservation line that was previously affliction efficiency.&amp;nbsp; There are some pretty desperare players out there at the moment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
